narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Offers both an overview and an in-depth look at Martial's work. Recommended if one is interested in Martial, or hasn't read much of him before as a place to start.
take it if you are a strong and competent latinist.

Definitely. Especially if this is the first Latin class you take at Yale -- Martial's epigrams are a nice way to ease into college-level Latin (how much better can you get than short, witty poems?). The pacing and amount of work for the class isn't overwhelming for the most part, and who doesn't enjoy reading sexually explicit invective (if you've stuck with Latin this far, you have to appreciate it at some level).
